<h3><!WA2><IMG SRC="http://www.cs.unm.edu/~steveah/bullet.gif" ALT="|">  Current Status</h3>
<p>
Since 1994 Steven Hofmeyr has been a graduate student in
the <!WA3><a href =
http://www.cs.unm.edu/Engr_Schl/CS_Dept/subpages/curriculum/gradhndbk/phd/Phd_front.html>Phd
program</a> in the <!WA4><a href = http://www.cs.unm.edu/>Computer Science
Department</a> at the <!WA5><A HREF = http://www.unm.edu/>University of New
Mexico</a>. 
<p>
He is
currently a Visiting Scholar at the <!WA6><a href =
"http://www.mit.edu/">MIT</a> <!WA7><a href = "http://www.ai.mit.edu">AI</a>
lab, where he will be until
the end of May 1997. His address at MIT is:
<p>
Steven A. Hofmeyr<br>
545 Technology Square, Room 831<br>
Cambridge MA 02139<br>
tel: 617 253 6625<br>
email: sah@ai.mit.edu
<p>
He is on the program committee for the <!WA8><a href =
http://www.cs.uwm.edu/~new-paradigms>New Security Paradigms Workshop '97</a>.
<p>
<h3><!WA9><IMG SRC="http://www.cs.unm.edu/~steveah/bullet.gif" ALT="|">  Education</h3>
<p>
Steven Hofmeyr received a BSc(Hons) and an Msc in <!WA10><a href =
http://www.cs.wits.ac.za>Computer Science</a> at the <!WA11><A HREF =
http://www.wits.ac.za/wits/wits1.html>University of the
Witwatersrand</a>, Johannesburg, <!WA12><A HREF =
http://www.is.co.za/www-za.html>South Africa</a>. 
<p>


